# CHALLENGE: Dissect Sparse Patterns
# Validates the `dissect` plugin handling of sparse patterns, specifically the use of
# empty mapping brackets `%{}` which tell the plugin to skip that portion of the string.
# In production configs, logs with variable padding or unneeded sections frequently use `%{}`.
# The tool MUST NOT crash on empty string keys in the pattern and should correctly identify
# only the named variables (`key1` and `key2`) as newly created fields.
# EXPECTED BEHAVIOR: Lineage tracks `key1` and `key2`, ignoring the skipped fields `%{}`.
filter {
  dissect {
    mapping => {
      "message" => "%{key1} %{} %{} %{key2} %{+key2}"
    }
  }
}
